Posts.Content: Tprewitt wrote: I had a core biopsy today. Before the biopsy the radiologist came in to talk to me. He said that due to the tight cluster and that they appeared more rapidity than they liked he was concerned about malignancy. After the biopsy he said that from what he saw he was hopeful it would come back benign. Can a radiologist tell that soon? Log in to post a reply
